6A-C
); suture between mesanepisternum and mesoventrite visible (Fig. 
5C
); metathoracic discrimen as long as 3/4 of sternite length (Fig. 
5C
); lanterns occupying the entire area of sternite VI and VII (Figs 
2A
, 
7A
